w York: Basic Books, 1978. \u00ef\u201a\u00b7 Foulkes, David. Dreaming: A Cognitive-Psychological", "Analysis. Hillsdale, NJ: Lawrence Erlbaum, 1985. \u00ef\u201a\u00b7 Foulkes, David. Children\u00e2\u20ac\u2122s Dreaming and the Development of Consciousness. Cambridge, MA: Harvard University Press,", "1999. \u00ef\u201a\u00b7 Freud, Sigmund. Dreams have been interpreted in many different ways from being a source of power to the capability of understanding and communicating with the dead.", "Traditional forms of societies considered dreams as portals to another world, a spirit world. These societies would even say they could gain most of their religious ideas from dreams.", "They could identify the sacred and gain access to sacred realms or portals to the supernatural. Psychologists have been researching dreams as of the 21st century because the PDF |", "The continuity hypothesis of dreaming suggests that waking day experiences are reflected in dream imagery; research suggests that some waking day | Find, read and cite all the", "research you need on ResearchGate.\u00c2 Spirituality is comprised of many dimensions, however, four very broad dimensions of spirituality are de\u00ee\u0192\u00a5ned as: (1). meaning and purpose", "in life, (2) intrinsic values (personal. belief systems and principles to live by), (3) transcendent.\u00c2 of religiosity than the dreams of a less religious sample (in. accordance with the", "continuity hypothesis of dreaming). In. Dreams is a long overdue collection of writing on dreams from many of the top scholars in religious studies, anthropology, and psychology", "departments. The volume is organized into three thematic sections: traditions, individuals and methods.\u00c2 You can write a book review and share your experiences. Other readers will", "always be interested in your opinion of the books you've read. Whether you've loved the book or not, if you give your honest and detailed thoughts then people will find new books", "that are right for them. 1.\u00c2 The mystical dimensions of dreaming are of particular interest to Kripal, Doniger, Irwin, Tedlock, and Hermansen. Re-evaluating Freud's dream theory is a", "primary goal of Hobson, Domhoff, Cohler, Jonte-Pace, DiCenso, Kracke, and Crews. Buy a cheap copy of Dreams: A Reader on Religious, Cultural book. The recent centennial of", "the original publication of Sigmund Freud's The Interpretation of Dreams has generated a new wave of critical reappraisals of this Free Shipping on all orders over $10.\u00c2 The recent", "centennial of the original publication of Sigmund Freud's The Interpretation of Dreams has generated a new wave of critical reappraisals of this monumental work. Considered one of", "the most important books in Western history, scholars from an astonishing variety of academic fields continue to wrestle with Freud's intricate theories and insights. Dreams is a long", "overdue collection of writing on dreams from many of the top scholars in religious Read Full Overview."], "bbox": [[0.013111, 0.006788, 0.917026, 0.017106], [0.013111, 0.028171, 0.8245840000000001, 0.017106], [0.013111, 0.048298, 0.947059, 0.008553], [0.013111, 0.059703, 0.962331, 0.008553], [0.013111, 0.071107, 0.961831, 0.008553], [0.013111, 0.082511, 0.950433, 0.008553], [0.013111, 0.093916, 0.9539460000000001, 0.008553], [0.013111, 0.10532, 0.9679110000000001, 0.008553], [0.013111, 0.116724, 0.9753350000000001, 0.008553], [0.013111, 0.128129, 0.950397, 0.008553], [0.013111, 0.139533, 0.9660150000000001, 0.008553], [0.013111, 0.150937, 0.9402780000000001, 0.008553], [0.013111, 0.162342, 0.9438070000000001, 0.008553], [0.013111, 0.173746, 0.972044, 0.008553], [0.013111, 0.18515, 0.951293, 0.008553], [0.013111, 0.196555, 0.969467, 0.008553], [0.013111, 0.207959, 0.9538840000000001, 0.008553], [0.013111, 0.219363, 0.964932, 0.008553], [0.013111, 0.230768, 0.966288, 0.008553], [0.013111, 0.242172, 0.9654950000000001, 0.008553], [0.013111, 0.253576, 0.5457700000000001, 0